Figure 2: The overall framework. We can perform pretraining on huge data via different pretext tasks and learn a highly semantic latent space that models general and high-quality image statistics. For downstream tasks, we perform conditional Ô¨Ånetuning to map the task-speciÔ¨Åc conditions to this pretrained semantic space. By leveraging the pretrained knowledge, our model renders plausible images based on different conditions.

To generate images from the data distribution, we can train a denoising model that starts from the Gaussian noise xT ‚àº N (0, I) and iteratively reduces the noise in the sequence of xT ‚àí1, ..., x1, x0. The denoising model Œ∏(xt, t) takes the noisy input xt at the timestep t and predicts the added noise using a mean square error loss:

