Qualitative results. We show visual results of different tasks in Figure 3 and Figure 4. Compared with from-scratch methods that suffer severe artifacts for complex scenes, the pretrained model signiÔ¨Åcantly improves the quality and diversity of generated images. As the COCO dataset contains many categories with diverse combinations, all the baseline methods fail to generate visually-pleasing results with compelling structures. In contrast, our methods can produce vivid details with correct semantics even for challenging cases. Figure 4 shows good applicability of our approach to different input modalities.
